{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/post/Rebuild-Blog-With-Gatsby-☄/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Rajitha's blog"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"cf099cc3-c94b-5554-8ea0-8bd326a25301","excerpt":"Hi everyone , I saw Gatsby quite some time ago and I was blown out by it’s speed. So I decided to move my blog to Gatsby and here’s how I did it. My first…","html":"<h2>Hi everyone ,</h2>\n<hr>\n<span style=\"font-size:1.28rem;\">\n<p>I saw <a href=\"https://www.gatsbyjs.org/\">Gatsby</a> quite some time ago and I was blown out by it’s speed. So I decided to move my blog to Gatsby and here’s how I did it.</p>\n<p>My first challenge was to grasp the concepts of Gatsby, and it’s SSR stuff. After that, I managed to duplicate the UI from my old blog, nothing fancy there.</p>\n<p>But the tricky part was how to manage data. previously i just rendered markdown in clientside via blog API.\nnow I create pages(blog posts) programmatically from gatsby <code class=\"language-text\">createPage</code> API to render markdown, but all the comments and views will be dynamically rendered on the client-side. and that was working well. now every blog post has it’s own HTML file, and because of that SEO is also enhanced.</p>\n<p>Now when I share Blog post URL it will show something similar.</p>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/22c0735739e4109d48854642b9de226f/f84cf/23288d23-33cd-48c2-8833-be81d0719236_jurbyb.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 145.27027027027026%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"telegram share url\" title=\"telegram share url\" src=\"/static/22c0735739e4109d48854642b9de226f/1c72d/23288d23-33cd-48c2-8833-be81d0719236_jurbyb.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/22c0735739e4109d48854642b9de226f/a80bd/23288d23-33cd-48c2-8833-be81d0719236_jurbyb.jpg 148w,\n/static/22c0735739e4109d48854642b9de226f/1c91a/23288d23-33cd-48c2-8833-be81d0719236_jurbyb.jpg 295w,\n/static/22c0735739e4109d48854642b9de226f/1c72d/23288d23-33cd-48c2-8833-be81d0719236_jurbyb.jpg 590w,\n/static/22c0735739e4109d48854642b9de226f/f84cf/23288d23-33cd-48c2-8833-be81d0719236_jurbyb.jpg 880w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\" style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \">\n      <a class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\" href=\"/static/30dbeae2146c2a604a755af793845b63/47311/839eaf21-14a1-4bf2-84f2-37f7dd8a78be_nueu8c.jpg\" style=\"display: block\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">\n    <span class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\" style=\"padding-bottom: 116.89189189189189%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/jpeg;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;\"></span>\n  <img class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\" alt=\"instagram share url\" title=\"instagram share url\" src=\"/static/30dbeae2146c2a604a755af793845b63/1c72d/839eaf21-14a1-4bf2-84f2-37f7dd8a78be_nueu8c.jpg\" srcset=\"/static/30dbeae2146c2a604a755af793845b63/a80bd/839eaf21-14a1-4bf2-84f2-37f7dd8a78be_nueu8c.jpg 148w,\n/static/30dbeae2146c2a604a755af793845b63/1c91a/839eaf21-14a1-4bf2-84f2-37f7dd8a78be_nueu8c.jpg 295w,\n/static/30dbeae2146c2a604a755af793845b63/1c72d/839eaf21-14a1-4bf2-84f2-37f7dd8a78be_nueu8c.jpg 590w,\n/static/30dbeae2146c2a604a755af793845b63/a8a14/839eaf21-14a1-4bf2-84f2-37f7dd8a78be_nueu8c.jpg 885w,\n/static/30dbeae2146c2a604a755af793845b63/47311/839eaf21-14a1-4bf2-84f2-37f7dd8a78be_nueu8c.jpg 1080w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\" style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\" loading=\"lazy\">\n  </a>\n    </span>\n<p>after finishing up all the development work. I started working on a deployment workflow. Earlier i manually build and push build files to <a href=\"https://pages.github.com/\">Github pages</a>. but with Gatsby modifications , it was not very practical since I need to build it every day because Blog’s landing page background is NASA’s <a href=\"https://apod.nasa.gov/apod/astropix.html\">Astronomy Picture of the Day</a> and that was updated every day. so I used Github actions for deployment.</p>\n<p>It eased the workflow quite a lot since now everything is built and published by one push to GitHub . And also a <code class=\"language-text\">cron</code> job ensures the building site every day to keep up with the NASA image.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://github.com/RizkyRajitha/RizkyRajitha.github.io\">Blog Repo</a></p>\n</span>\n<h2>Thanks for reading folks see y’all in next one 🙌.</h2>","frontmatter":{"id":"5f4270dca76a0d0017702d28","title":"Rebuild Blog With Gatsby ☄","date":"August 23, 2020","description":null,"ogimage":"Rebuild-Blog-With-Gatsby.png"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/post/Rebuild-Blog-With-Gatsby-☄/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/post/optimizing-blog/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Optimizing blog"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/post/Realtime-Anemometer-Project/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Realtime Anemometer Project"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["2841359383"]}